The problem requires finding the minimum time needed to repair all cars using the given ranks. We can calculate the total repair time by summing up the squared ranks of each mechanic and multiplying it by the number of cars. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the ranks once, and the space complexity is O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space to store the sum.

